# Excludes files from the Netlify deploy UPLOAD even though publish = "."
# (repo root) technically covers them -- gitignore syntax, applied after
# the build command runs. This is distinct from .gitignore: node_modules
# is never uploaded because it's git-ignored (Netlify builds from a git
# clone), but care-hub-app/ itself IS committed to git (it's the Care
# Hub's real source) and must still be kept out of the served static
# site -- only its build OUTPUT (../care-hub, built by netlify.toml's
# build.command) should ever be publicly reachable.
care-hub-app/
